# Keep the refresh AND embed image build contexts small (docker/refresh.Dockerfile
# and docker/embed.Dockerfile).
#
# Both images' build context is the repo ROOT (compose: `context: ..`), but they only
# COPY a handful of small .py files + src/rcp.html. Without these excludes the context
# would include dist/ (~720M), data/ (~260M) and models/ (~120M, mounted read-only at
# runtime, never baked): every `docker compose up --build` would tar and ship ~1GB+ to
# the daemon, which is slow and can FAIL the build on a small VPS ("no space left on
# device"), aborting `up` so no containers get created. Only the big/irrelevant paths
# are listed; the handful of small files the Dockerfiles need stay in.
.git
dist
data
vendor
models
docker/.env
**/__pycache__
*.pyc
*.pyo
.venv
.serena
node_modules
